figure><\/li><\/ul><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"besttime\">Best time to travel in Uzbekistan<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>It is best to visit Uzbekistan in their spring (April to June) and autumn (September &#x2013; October) when the weather comfortably warm and dry. In general, it is recommended skipping the summer months June to August however our visit late August was fine if we would stay out of the sun in the afternoon.&#xA0;<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"outfit\">What to wear in Uzbekistan<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Uzbekistan is a modern country without strict rules on how women should dress. Although the majority of the country is Muslim, headscarves are not required at all, and you will see women wearing whatever they feel comfortable with, even ripped jeans or skirts. Expect quite a few selfie questions as western tourists are still new and exciting.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/23125748\/uzbekistan-travel-what-to-wear-648x810.jpg\" alt=\"uzbekistan travel what to wear\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"uzbekistan travel what to wear\" data-id=\"17822\" data-link=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?attachment_id=17822\" class=\"wp-image-17822 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 648px) 100vw, 648px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/23125748\/uzbekistan-travel-what-to-wear-648x810.jpg 648w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/23125748\/uzbekistan-travel-what-to-wear-300x375.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/